"vote_count":3278,"poster_path":"/zx4V17FP8oclNvOpTgs2iCCtiYk.jpg","release_date":"1963-10-10","vote_average":7.065,"backdrop_path":"/8JMiQa0OqsCYvbNUrQIrMzwV7g2.jpg","original_title":"From Russia with Love","original_language":"en"},{"id":658,"adult":false,"title":"Goldfinger","video":false,"overview":"Special agent 007 comes face to face with one of the most notorious villains of all time, and now he must outwit and outgun the powerful tycoon to prevent him from cashing in on a devious scheme to raid Fort Knox -- and obliterate the world's economy.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":6.2145,"vote_count":3870,"poster_path":"/aKNFzaqQgPzsGXnsMc4kJH5hFIV.jpg","release_date":"1964-09-20","vote_average":7.355,"backdrop_path":"/f1Is9VLQZSRpeLMU7mIcj5aXclt.jpg","original_title":"Goldfinger","original_language":"en"},{"id":667,"adult":false,"title":"You Only Live Twice","video":false,"overview":"A mysterious spacecraft captures Russian and American space capsules and brings the two superpowers to the brink of war. James Bond investigates the case in Japan and comes face to face with his archenemy Blofeld.","genre_ids":[28,53,12],"popularity":7.1355,"vote_count":2402,"poster_path":"/fdRbvRcEXcf2rC4ghLFZzCWPSmB.jpg","release_date":"1967-06-13","vote_average":6.593,"backdrop_path":"/cpZAXIYA0lkZMpAt7d1MmH8ojNV.jpg","original_title":"You Only Live Twice","original_language":"en"},{"id":668,"adult":false,"title":"On Her Majesty's Secret Service","video":false,"overview":"With the help of Marc-Ange Draco, head of the Unione Corse crime syndicate, and Draco's troubled daughter Tracy, James Bond tracks his archnemesis, Ernst Stravro Blofeld, to a mountaintop retreat in the Swiss Alps, where he is training an army of beautiful, lethal women.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":5.3271,"vote_count":2077,"poster_path":"/m3KfbxvqaiAvRJ6MpguA3GuLdDQ.jpg","release_date":"1969-12-18","vote_average":6.562,"backdrop_path":"/58pMrmwwcKamJIdjUlinE6QX1Fs.jpg","original_title":"On Her Majesty's Secret Service","original_language":"en"},{"id":679,"adult":false,"title":"Aliens","video":false,"overview":"Ripley, the sole survivor of the Nostromo's deadly encounter with the monstrous Alien, returns to Earth after drifting through space in hypersleep for 57 years. Although her story is initially met with skepticism, she agrees to accompany a team of Colonial Marines back to LV-426.","genre_ids":[28,53,878],"popularity":12.7427,"vote_count":10609,"poster_path":"/r1x5JGpyqZU8PYhbs4UcrO1Xb6x.jpg","release_date":"1986-07-18","vote_average":7.956,"backdrop_path":"/4kix6fAblJIH6eMs0Ku2loyZJXK.jpg","original_title":"Aliens","original_language":"en"},{"id":682,"adult":false,"title":"The Man with the Golden Gun","video":false,"overview":"Cool government operative James Bond searches for a stolen invention that can turn the sun's heat into a destructive weapon. He soon crosses paths with the menacing Francisco Scaramanga, a hitman so skilled he has a seven-figure working fee. Bond then joins forces with the swimsuit-clad Mary Goodnight, and together they track Scaramanga to a Thai tropical isle hideout where the killer-for-hire lures the slick spy into a deadly maze for a final duel.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":4.9709,"vote_count":2220,"poster_path":"/xVkbKwGnBVNQ122GN5bCTMyPbWz.jpg","release_date":"1974-12-04","vote_average":6.456,"backdrop_path":"/3tpNEbRahT8smy7RraaWa0xg9Gv.jpg","original_title":"The Man with the Golden Gun","original_language":"en"},{"id":691,"adult":false,"title":"The Spy Who Loved Me","video":false,"overview":"Russian and British submarines with nuclear missiles on board both vanish from sight without a trace. England and Russia both blame each other as James Bond tries to solve the riddle of the disappearing ships. But the KGB also has an agent on the case.","genre_ids":[12,28,53],"popularity":5.5757,"vote_count":2166,"poster_path":"/3ZxHKFxMYvAko680DsRgAZKWcLi.jpg","release_date":"1977-07-07","vote_average":6.825,"backdrop_path":"/8lRdfsmJjUXQU3DMOOB3vVIhJxP.jpg","original_title":"The Spy Who Loved Me","original_language":"en"},{"id":694,"adult":false,"title":"The Shining","video":false,"overview":"Jack Torrance accepts a caretaker job at the Overlook Hotel, where he, along with his wife Wendy and their son Danny, must live isolated from the rest of the world for the winter. But they aren't prepared for the madness that lurks within.","genre_ids":[27,53],"popularity":14.883,"vote_count":18628,"poster_path":"/uAR0AWqhQL1hQa69UDEbb2rE5Wx.jpg","release_date":"1980-05-23","vote_average":8.2,"backdrop_path":"/mmd1HnuvAzFc4iuVJcnBrhDNEKr.jpg","original_title":"The Shining","original_language":"en"},{"id":696,"adult":false,"title":"Manhattan","video":false,"overview":"Manhattan explores how the life of a middle-aged television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.","genre_ids":[35,18,10749],"popularity":3.8199,"vote_count":2566,"poster_path":"/k4eT3EvfxW1L9Wmt04UqJqCvCR6.jpg","release_date":"1979-04-25","vote_average":7.718,"backdrop_path":"/adnSTomHU9YyqV2lx38CgM0UxLS.jpg","original_title":"Manhattan","original_language":"en"},{"id":698,"adult":false,"title":"Moonraker","video":false,"overview":"After Drax Industries' Moonraker space shuttle is hijacked, secret agent James Bond is assigned to investigate, traveling to California to meet the company's owner, the mysterious Hugo Drax. With the help of scientist Dr. Holly Goodhead, Bond soon uncovers Drax's nefarious plans for humanity, all the while fending off an old nemesis, Jaws, and venturing to Venice, Rio, the Amazon...and even outer space.","genre_ids":[28,12,53,878],"popularity":5.3553,"vote_count":2152,"poster_path":"/6LrJdXNmu5uHOVALZxVYd44Lva0.jpg","release_date":"1979-06-26","vote_average":6.181,"backdrop_path":"/mrDC5DLx2wljt4HZGwgkmqlzfcF.jpg","original_title":"Moonraker","original_language":"en"}],"external_ids":{"imdb_id":"tt1527793","twitter_id":"noother_choice","face